div.div: Commented on #514 Cannot call proxies for Kotlin extension functions (e.g. AndroidX UiObject2.onElement)

Javet doesn't support kotlin specific features because Javet is written on JDK 8. Thanks for the response this is an excellent project. I implemented a proxy/wrapper for UiObject2 and added an onElement method, which solved the immediate problem. However, a new issue has arisen. When I call onElement from a JS script, since onElement is a Java method it sometimes throws errors (for example, NoElementException). That's expected, but I'm actually building an Android automation script engine and I don't want to expose Java-level stack traces directly to users. I want these errors to be customizable when they're caught on the JS side. For example, when I use try-catch in JS, the thrown Error should be NoElementException instead of "Uncaught JavaError in function callback" in such cases. When I catch the error on the JS side, I seem unable to modify the exception object.
